title.value: ESTRO 2023: 3D Printed Materials for E2E Test Phantoms in Proton Therapy
title.justification: The title captures the main topic of the paper, which is about 3D printed materials used for test phantoms in proton therapy, as reported in the ESTRO 2023 conference.
title.quote: The investigated 3D printed materials will enable efficient manufacturing of E2E test phantoms for proton therapy.

extractions.description: The paper discusses the evaluation of 3D printed materials for use in manufacturing end-to-end test phantoms in proton therapy, focusing on their water equivalent ratio and the suitability of different materials for mimicking soft tissue, breast/fatty tissue, and skin/cartilage.

type.justification: The study provides empirical measurements and comparisons of predicted versus measured water equivalent ratios for different 3D printed materials.
type.quote: Measurements revealed a water equivalent ratio (WER = WET/density) ranging from 0.91 to 1.52 with a measurement uncertainty below 1%.

name.justification: The research is centered around developing test phantoms for proton therapy, which is a key area within Medical Physics.
